OL,3,CAmbulance workers resign after court
OL,4,Cruling over man's death
OL,6,FHowever, the prosecution argued that
OL,7,FSutherland and Le Sauteur failed to
OL,8,Fput him in the recovery position, did
OL,9,Fnot recognise he was struggling to
OL,10,Fbreathe and failed to provide adequate
OL,11,Fcare during resuscitation.
OL,13,FThe pair were both found guilty of
OL,14,Fbreaching health and safety law and
OL,15,Freceived a conditional discharge when
OL,16,Fthey were sentenced in July, which
OL,17,Fmeans they will be back in court if
OL,18,Fthey commit any further offences.
