OL,6,F"The Ambulance Service senior
OL,7,Fleadership team and Unite the Union
OL,8,Fwill continue to work closely and
OL,9,Fproactively together to address any
OL,10,Fconcerns raised by colleagues and the
OL,11,FUnite membership."
OL,13,FThe workers had been suspended from
OL,14,Fthe service since 23 March 2022,
OL,15,Fshortly after the incident happened,
OL,16,Fand received an outpouring of support
OL,17,Ffollowing their conviction last year.
